  "metadata": {
    "what_it_measures": "Personal Consumption Expenditures Price Index excluding Food and Energy. BEA. Monthly, end-of-month 8:30 ET. The Fed's preferred inflation gauge.\n",
    "why_it_matters": "Core PCE drives Fed reaction function. The 2% target is specifically for PCE, not CPI. Differences from CPI: PCE uses chain-weighting and covers broader spending (not just out-of-pocket).\n",
    "scoring_rule": "< 2.0% \u2192 +60 | 2.0-2.3% \u2192 +30 | 2.3-2.5% \u2192 0 | 2.5-3.0% \u2192 -30 | 3.0-3.5% \u2192 -60 | > 3.5% \u2192 -90. Phase 3.\n"
  },
